## Frequently asked questions

### What Workfront items can I work with through Claude?

<!-- NEEDS DETAIL: List the supported Workfront object types. -->

### Can I connect to multiple Workfront instances at once?

No. Each connection ties [!DNL Claude] to a single Workfront instance. To switch, disconnect the connector and reconnect, authenticating to the new instance.

### Does this work with Claude Pro or Claude Team, or only Claude Enterprise?

<!-- NEEDS DETAIL: Confirm Claude tier support and answer this directly. -->

### Who needs to enable this — my Workfront administrator or my Claude administrator?

Both. Your [!DNL Claude] Enterprise administrator enables the connector in [!DNL Claude]. Your Workfront system administrator controls MCP access on the Workfront side.

### Is my Workfront data sent to Anthropic or stored by Claude?

<!-- NEEDS DETAIL: Document the official Adobe position on data handling and security when Workfront data is passed through Claude. This needs sign-off from security/legal before publication. -->

### What happens when a new version of the connector releases?

The connector updates automatically. You don't need to reconnect or change anything.

### Do I need to know the Workfront API to use this?

No. [!DNL Claude] translates your natural-language requests into the right Workfront actions. If you're already familiar with the Workfront API, the actions will feel familiar — but it isn't a requirement.
